headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 21 points, Isaac Okoro added 20 and the Cleveland Cavaliers won their fifth straight game, a 124-89 rout of the Houston Rockets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers win fifth straight, rout Rockets 124-89

headlines.description: — Trae Young played through a neck injury to score 28 points, John Collins had 21 points and 10 rebounds and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Orlando Magic 111-99 on Wednesday night to end a two-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young overcomes neck injury, Hawks beat Magic 111-99

headlines.description: — Gabe Vincent hit a key 3-pointer in the fourth quarter and scored 26 points, Duncan Robinson had 21 points, and the short-handed Miami Heat built a 23-point lead and held on to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 101-96 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vincent, Robinson lead short-handed Heat past 76ers 101-96

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Rookie Austin Reaves swished a 3-pointer with 0.9 seconds left in overtime to give the Los Angeles Lakers a 107-104 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Austin Reaves' 3 gives Lakers 107-104 win over Mavs in OT

headlines.description: — Playing without stars Giannis Antetokounmpo and Khris Middleton, the Milwaukee Bucks leaned on Jrue Holiday and had a 21-0 fourth-quarter run to beat the Indiana Pacers 114-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jrue Holiday helps short-handed Bucks beat Pacers, 114-99

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Devonte' Graham's 61-foot heave at the buzzer gave the New Orleans Pelicans a 113-110 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Graham's 61-footer at the buzzer leads Pelicans past Thunder

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Charlotte is finally getting healthy, and Gordon Hayward celebrated by leading the Hornets to one of their strongest performances of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayward's season-high 41 leads Hornets past Spurs 131-115

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards made 10 3-pointers and scored 38 points, and the Minnesota Timberwolves snapped a 12-game losing streak to Denver, beating the Nuggets 124-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 38 points, T-wolves beat Nuggets 124-107

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell played a nearly perfect second half to keep Utah’s winning streak going, though he has bigger goals than regular-season victories.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Jazz beat Clippers 124-103 for eighth straight win

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 23 points and the Memphis Grizzlies stretched their winning streak to four games with a 113-103 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Desmond Bane scores 23, Memphis beats Trail Blazers 113-103

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox scored 28 points and the short-handed Sacramento Kings beat the slumping Washington Wizards 119-105 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox, Barnes help Kings pull away to beat Wizards 119-105
